# Copy this file to fdroiddata/metadata/dev.halim.shelfdroid.yml when opening
# the F-Droid merge request, then update the release-specific fields below.

Categories:
  - Multimedia

AuthorName: Fernando Fransisco Halim
AuthorWebSite: https://github.com/100nandoo
License: AGPL-3.0-or-later
SourceCode: https://github.com/100nandoo/shelfdroid
IssueTracker: https://github.com/100nandoo/shelfdroid/issues

MaintainerNotes: |-
  - Upstream app metadata lives in fastlane/metadata/android/en-US.
  - Release tags are exact version names such as 0.4.3.
  - versionCode and versionName are sourced from app/version.properties, so
    checkupdates must use UpdateCheckData instead of default Gradle parsing.
  - GitHub Release APKs are published as shelfdroid-<tag>.apk and are the
    upstream binaries intended for F-Droid verification and publication.
  - The GitHub signing workflow pins Android build-tools 34.0.0 because
    F-Droid's reproducible-build docs warn that apksigner from build-tools 35+
    can break signature-copy verification.
  - On 2026-06-22, a clean rebuild of tag 0.4.2 matched the published
    developer-signed 0.4.2 APK at the extracted non-META-INF file level and in
    non-META-INF ZIP entry order; only META-INF signature files differed.

RepoType: git
Repo: https://github.com/100nandoo/shelfdroid.git
Binaries: https://github.com/100nandoo/shelfdroid/releases/download/%v/shelfdroid-%v.apk

Builds:
  - versionName: 0.4.3
    versionCode: 16
    commit: 681806a0650fa1a28c9ab85c438dbb0e7c1f8d74
    subdir: app
    gradle:
      - yes
    output: build/outputs/apk/release/app-release-unsigned.apk

AllowedAPKSigningKeys: 0430bed01abb1c653fc56883314a1c14f4922314f5af16af68885c732dd29bbd
AutoUpdateMode: Version
UpdateCheckMode: Tags ^[0-9]+(\.[0-9]+)*$
UpdateCheckData: app/version.properties|VERSION_CODE=(\d+)|.|VERSION_NAME=(.+)
CurrentVersion: 0.4.3
CurrentVersionCode: 16
